race.description: Ray White Berry - Sarah Tebbutt Maiden Plate
race.comment: Tricky race to assess with a few first starters engaged. NEESON (11) showed ability at his only start back on April 26 when second at Canberra. Has impressed in his trials in readiness and from an ideal draw he can make the perfect return. COSMIC ATTRACTION (6) is a first-starter by Cosmic Force from the Crothers team. Chased NEESON gamely to the line in a recent Goulburn trial. Have to consider off that. TREASURE HUNTER (12) also debuts. Is a Prince Fawaz gelding hailing from the Scott Collings stable that has been readied with a pair of solid Moruya trials. Market support will be key. RUN RAYMOND RUN (3) is backing up nine days after finishing fifth over 1300m at Canberra. Form prior is much better and off that warrants safe keeping. DUBAI JORGE (10) is a son of Pride Of Dubai on debut from the Nickson camp. Only seen once at the trials, where he work soundly to the line at Moruya behind a sharp one. Inside alley is a bonus. Respect market support.
